[ Full belly ]

1. Dry pork belly and leave out overnight in fridge, skin side up

2. Oven on to 140째C

3. Oil & season (salt + pep) flesh and skin, wrap flesh in foil
    - 1:1 white:black pep, 1.0g of each for an 850g belly
    - 2.0g salt for an 850g belly (felsh sides only)
    - Start skin side down
    - Oil, salt, pep, rub in (incl. sides)
    - Flip onto foil, wrap around sides to confit (skin side up)
    - Rub on 1 tsp oil
    - Evenly sprinkle salt

4. Low roast for 1.5 + 1 hrs
    - 1.5 hrs
    - take out, tighten confit foil
    - 1 hr
    
5. Oven up to 240째C

6. Level belly (using foil balls) so skin is flat

7. Blast crackling for 20 - 30 mins (until golden brown and crackled)

8. Rest 10 mins


[ Fallow belly slices ]
- blanch to soften skin
- follow above recipe for seasoning
- bake for 30 mins at 210째C
- reduce temp to 180째C and bake for a further 25 mins

